directory: crates/ctx-verify/tests
domain: Integration-level test suite for ctx-verify's diagnostic parsers and check-orchestration logic, exercised end-to-end through a fake command Runner instead of real subprocesses. Verifies serde output shapes and status-rollup precedence that other crates may rely on when consuming CheckReport JSON.
edit_notes:
  - FakeRunner keys canned outcomes by first arg via by_first_arg: BTreeMap<String, Option<CommandOutcome>>; unmatched or None keys simulate CheckError::ToolMissing.
  - Tests assert exact JSON string shapes for CheckReport; any change to its Serialize impl or field names must update these tests in lockstep.
children:
  - checks.rs: sole test file, covering parser correctness and orchestration status/diagnostic-capping behavior.
invariants:
  - Status::Errored outranks Status::Fail in overall rollup; skipped-only reports yield Status::Pass.
  - Non-zero exit with unparseable output still yields Status::Fail with a synthesized diagnostic, never an empty diagnostics list.